<br>
In the original concept, dragons were just more powerful in the endgame - unbalancing as hell.  To counter it, they were HELLA hard to level up, and it was fully PvP against them, since even newbie dragons dropped dragon scales which were highly valuable.  To put it simply, they'd be hunted by all the other players.  It would have likely taken guild support to raise a dragon.<br>
<br>
That's gone.  As far as I know, PvP is gone.  There are a lot of good things about being a humanoid over a dragon, but not enough to keep half the game population from being dragons.  They need to do something.<br>
<br>
Tradeskills.  Omg.  EQ = owned.  <br>
<br>
I've been playing around with half giants.  This is what I love about horizons.  The classes are scaled appropriately.  Half giants are gigantic....maybe half a foot shy of being twice the height of humans.  Screenshots don't do it justice.  They look like they could rip the wings right off a dragon.  Well, a newbie dragon at least - they start out the size of a shetland ponie maybe.<br>
